para_trans: Regarding the declaration of a local holiday on the occasion of Dr. Babasaheb Ambedkar Mahaparinirvan Diwas. . .
Government Circular No: Local - 1324 / P.No.32 / Japuk (29)
Mantralaya, Madam Cama Marg, Martyrdom Rajguru Chowk,

Government Circular: Government Circular, General Administration Department No. Sarsu-1196 / Q. No. 5/96/29, dated 18th September, 1996 declares "Anant Chaturdashi" as a local holiday for the Government / Municipal Offices of Mumbai City and Mumbai Suburban District every year and on the occasion of Gopalaka (Dahi Handi) for Mumbai City and Mumbai Suburban Districts since 2007. Now in the year 2024, all government / semi-government offices in Mumbai and Mumbai Suburban districts are being declared as the third local holiday by it as follows.

2. These orders shall apply to the State Government / Municipal offices in the city of Mumbai and the Mumbai Suburban District 3. Local Holidays Government Decision No. P & S No. P-13 / above. / b, dated 5th November, 1958 is being declared as per the provision.
The circular was made available on the Government of Maharashtra website www.maharashtra.gov.in.
